The evidence with the title 'Poll: majority skeptical of GOP healthcare bill | TheHill ' says Mar 20, 2017  ... In general , voters are split on the fate of ObamaCare, with 41 percent saying they support legislation to repeal and replace the healthcare law, versus 43 percent who say they oppose a new healthcare overhaul. Still, the poll found there is opportunity for Republicans if they can sell their ideas effectively. 
